---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import ArrowIcon from "../assets/svg/arrow.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Service | Penqwin"
  description="Read the terms of service for Penqwin's documentation platform. Understand your rights and responsibilities when using our service."
>
  <Header />
  <main class="relative min-h-screen bg-bg-main pt-32 pb-24 overflow-hidden">
    <!-- Background Effects (Matching Hero) -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 pointer-events-none overflow-hidden">
      <div
        class="absolute inset-0 bg-grid opacity-[0.02] [mask-image:radial-gradient(ellipse_at_center,black,transparent_80%)]"
      >
      </div>
      <div
        class="absolute top-[-10%] left-[-10%] w-[600px] h-[600px] bg-primary/5 blur-[120px] rounded-full animate-pulse-slow"
      >
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
      <!-- Back Link -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <a
          href="/"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-text-secondary hover:text-primary transition-colors duration-300 group"
        >
          <ArrowIcon
            class="w-4 h-4 rotate-180 transform group-hover:-translate-x-1 transition-transform"
          />
          <span class="text-sm font-medium">Back to Home</span>
        </a>
      </div>

      <!-- Header -->
      <header class="mb-16">
        <h1
          class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-6xl text-text-primary tracking-tight mb-4"
        >
          Terms of Service
        </h1>
        <p class="text-text-secondary font-medium">
          Effective Date: <span class="text-text-primary">March 2026</span>
        </p>
      </header>

      <!-- Content -->
      <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none space-y-12">
        <section>
          <p
            class="text-lg text-text-secondary leading-relaxed first-letter:text-4xl first-letter:font-serif first-letter:text-primary first-letter:mr-2 first-letter:float-left"
          >
            These Terms of Service (“Terms”) govern your access to and use of
            Penqwin (“the Platform”). By accessing our Platform, you agree to be
            bound by these Terms.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2
            class="font-serif text-2xl text-text-primary flex items-center gap-3"
          >
            <span class="text-text-muted text-sm font-mono tracking-tighter"
              >01.</span
            >
            Global License & Access
          </h2>
          <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
            Penqwin grants you a non-exclusive, worldwide, royalty-free license
            to use the Platform. We aim to empower developers everywhere to
            automate the most tedious parts of the software lifecycle.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2
            class="font-serif text-2xl text-text-primary flex items-center gap-3"
          >
            <span class="text-text-muted text-sm font-mono tracking-tighter"
              >02.</span
            >
            Intellectual Property & Data Privacy
          </h2>
          <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
            You retain full ownership of all source code, repository metadata,
            and generated documentation. Penqwin acts as a processor to
            transform your technical inputs into structured knowledge. We do not
            claim any rights to your proprietary intellectual property.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2
            class="font-serif text-2xl text-text-primary flex items-center gap-3 mb-4"
          >
            <span class="text-text-muted text-sm font-mono tracking-tighter"
              >03.</span
            >
            Service Standards & Evolution
          </h2>
          <div class="space-y-4 text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
            <p>
              We are committed to rapid innovation. To maintain this pace, the
              Platform is provided on an "as-is" basis.
            </p>
            <p>
              By using the Platform, you acknowledge that Penqwin is a tool for
              professional assistance and that all generated documentation
              should be verified for accuracy before production use.
            </p>
            <p>
              We reserve the right to evolve, update, or retire features as we
              continuously improve the Platform.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2
            class="font-serif text-2xl text-text-primary flex items-center gap-3"
          >
            <span class="text-text-muted text-sm font-mono tracking-tighter"
              >04.</span
            >
            User Responsibilities
          </h2>
          <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
            You represent that you have the legal right to access and process
            any repository URLs provided to the Platform. You agree not to use
            Penqwin for any unauthorized data extraction or to violate the
            security of third-party platforms like GitHub.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2
            class="font-serif text-2xl text-text-primary flex items-center gap-3"
          >
            <span class="text-text-muted text-sm font-mono tracking-tighter"
              >05.</span
            >
            Limitation of Liability
          </h2>
          <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
            To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, Penqwin and its
            creators shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, or
            consequential damages resulting from your use of the service. This
            includes, without limitation, any loss of data, service
            interruptions, or inaccuracies in AI-generated content. Our total
            liability for any claim arising out of these terms shall be limited
            to the amount paid by you to use the service.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2
            class="font-serif text-2xl text-text-primary flex items-center gap-3"
          >
            <span class="text-text-muted text-sm font-mono tracking-tighter"
              >06.</span
            >
            Universal Jurisdiction
          </h2>
          <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
            Penqwin is a global platform. These Terms shall be governed by and
            construed in accordance with the laws of the jurisdiction where the
            primary developer is based (India), without regard to its conflict
            of law provisions. Any legal action or proceeding arising under
            these Terms will be brought exclusively in the courts of that
            jurisdiction.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>

      <!-- Contact/Support -->
      <!-- <div class="mt-24 pt-12 border-t border-white/10 text-center">
        <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm">
          Questions about our Terms? <a
            href="mailto:support@penqwin.com"
            class="text-primary hover:underline transition-all">Get in touch</a
          >
        </p>
      </div> -->
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  /* Custom prose-like styles for minimal control */
  .prose p {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  /* Selection color */
  ::selection {
    background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.2);
    color: #fff;
  }
</style>
